trans-unit.source: Defines a set of <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> fields that each corresponds to a command function provided by the workflow designers.
This class cannot be inherited.

<xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.WorkflowMenuCommands> contains a set of <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID> fields that can be used to specify a command to link when adding a command using the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.MenuCommandService.AddCommand%2A> method of the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.IMenuCommandService>.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.WorkflowMenuCommands"></xref> class.
Gets the <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> for the breakpoint action menu.
This field is read-only.
The breakpoint action menu is typically used to set, remove, or change breakpoints.
Gets the <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> for the breakpoint condition menu.
This field is read-only.
The breakpoint condition menu is typically used to set, remove, or change conditional breakpoints.
Gets the <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> for the breakpoint constraints menu.
This field is read-only.
The breakpoint constraints menu is typically used to set, remove or change constraints on breakpoints.
Gets the <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> for the breakpoint hit count menu.
This field is read-only.
The breakpoint hit count menu typically displays the hit count for breakpoints.
Gets the <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> for the breakpoint location menu.
This field is read-only.
The breakpoint location menu is typically used to modify the location of breakpoints.
Gets the <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> for the change theme menu.
This field is read-only.
The theme change menu is typically used to change the theme for the designer.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the clear breakpoints menu.
This field is read-only.
The clear breakpoints menu is typically used to clear all breakpoints set in the debugger.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the collapse menu.
This field is read-only.
The collapse menu is typically used to collapse composite activities.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the copy menu.
This field is read-only.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the create theme menu.
This field is read-only.
The create theme menu is typically used to create a new theme for the designer.
Provides a unique identifier for the debug command set.
This field is read-only.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the debug step branch menu.
This field is read-only.
The debug step branch menu is typically used to step into a branch in the debugger.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the debug step instance menu.
This field is read-only.
The debug step instance menu is typically used to step into an instance of an object in the debugger.
Provides a unique identifier for the debug workflow group of menus.
This field is read-only.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the default filter menu.
This field is read-only.
The default filter menu is typically used to set or modify the default filter for the workflow.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the default page menu.
This field is read-only.
The default page menu is typically used to set or modify the default page for the workflow.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the designer actions menu.
This field is read-only.
The designer actions menu is typically used to access actions available to the designer.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the designer properties menu.
This field is read-only.
The designer properties menu typically provides a dialog to set designer properties.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the disable menu.
This field is read-only.
The disable menu typically disables an activity on a workflow.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the enable menu.
This field is read-only.
The enable menu typically enables an activity on a workflow.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the enable breakpoint menu.
This field is read-only.
The enable breakpoint menu typically enables a previously set breakpoint.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the execution state menu.
This field is read-only.
The execution state menu typically indicates the state of the workflow.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the expand menu.
This field is read-only.
The expand menu typically causes collapsed sections of code to expand.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the zoom first menu.
This field is read-only.
The zoom first command typically restores the workflow view to the first zoom level.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the goto disassembly menu.
This field is read-only.
The goto disassembly menu is typically used to navigate to disassembled code in the debugger.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the insert breakpoint menu.
This field is read-only.
The insert breakpoint menu is typically used to insert a breakpoint into the workflow at the cursor or before the current selection.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the insert tracepoint menu.
This field is read-only.
The insert tracepoint menu is typically used to insert a tracepoint at the cursor or before the current selection.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the zoom last menu.
This field is read-only.
The last zoom command typically restores the workflow view to the last zoom level.
Provides a unique identifier for the menu.
This field is read-only.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the new data breakpoint menu.
This field is read-only.
The new data breakpoint menu typically inserts a new data-driven breakpoint.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the new file tracepoint menu.
This field is read-only.
The new file tracepoint menu typically inserts a new tracepoint.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the PageDown menu.
This field is read-only.
The page down menu is typically used to scroll the workflow down one page.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the page layout menu.
This field is read-only.
The page layout menu is typically used to adjust the page layout options.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the page setup menu.
This field is read-only.
The page setup menu is typically used to bring forward the page setup dialog.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the PageUp menu.
This field is read-only.
The page up menu is typically used to scroll the workflow up one page.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the pan menu.
This field is read-only.
The pan menu is typically used to scroll the visible area of the workflow.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the pan menu.
This field is read-only.
The pan menu is typically used to scroll the visible area of the workflow.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the print menu.
This field is read-only.
The print menu is typically used to print the workflow.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the print preview menu.
This field is read-only.
The print preview menu is typically used to preview the printing of a workflow.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the print preview page menu.
This field is read-only.
The print preview page menu is typically used to page through a print preview.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the run to cursor menu.
This field is read-only.
The run to cursor menu is typically used to place a breakpoint in the workflow at the location of the cursor and resume execution until that breakpoint is reached.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the save as image menu.
This field is read-only.
The save as image menu saves the workflow as an image.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the selection menu.
This field is read-only.
The selection menu is typically used to manage a selection within the workflow.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the set next statement menu.
This field is read-only.
The set next statement menu is typically used to set the next statement to execute while stepping through the execution of a workflow.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the show all menu.
This field is read-only.
The show all menu is typically used to show all child objects in the workflow.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the show next statement menu.
This field is read-only.
The show next statement menu is typically used to highlight the next statement to be executed while stepping through the execution of a workflow.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the toggle breakpoint menu.
This field is read-only.
The toggle breakpoint menu is typically used to turn on or off a breakpoint.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the verb group actions menu.
This field is read-only.
The verb group actions menu is typically used to access actions arranged by verb group.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the verb group designer actions menu.
This field is read-only.
The verb group designer actions menu is typically used to access designer actions arranged by verb group.

This field is read-only.
The edit verb group is typically used to access the verbs in the edit group.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the general verb group menu.
This field is read-only.
The general verb group menu is typically used to access verbs in the general group.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the miscellaneous verb group menu.
This field is read-only.
The miscellaneous verb group menu is typically used to access verbs in the miscellaneous group.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the options verb group menu.
This field is read-only.
The options very group menu is typically used to access verbs in the options group.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the view verb group menu.
This field is read-only.
The view verb group menu is typically used to access verbs in the view group.
Provides a unique identifier for the workflow command set.
This field is read-only.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the workflow toolbar menu.
This field is read-only.
The workflow toolbar menu appears at the bottom of the workflow design surface.

This field is read-only.
The zoom 100% menu is typically used to set the zoom level to 100% on a workflow.

The zoom 300% menu is typically used to set the zoom level to 300% on a workflow.

This field is read-only.
The zoom 400% menu is typically used to set the zoom level to 400% on a workflow.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the zoom 50% menu.
This field is read-only.
The zoom 50% menu is typically used to set the zoom level to 50% on a workflow.
A <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID"></xref> that can be used to access the zoom 75% menu.
This field is read-only.
The zoom 75% menu is typically used to set the zoom level to 75% on a workflow.

The zoom level combo menu is typically used to bring forward a dialog from which the user can select a zoom level from a combo box.

This field is read-only.

The zoom menu typically provides a choice of zoom levels for the workflow view.

This field is read-only.
The zoom out menu is typically used to decrease the magnification of the workflow.
